\begin{align*}
1+t &= -1\\
\Rightarrow\qquad t &= -2\\
\Rightarrow\qquad 7-2(-2) &= 8+u\\
\Rightarrow\qquad 9 &= 8+u\\
\Rightarrow\qquad u &= 1
\end{align*}

Substituting $t=-2$ and $u=1$ into the original equations, we have

\begin{align*}
\bold{v} &= \begin{pmatrix} 7 \\ -3 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} + (-2) \begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ 5 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 7+4 \\ -3-10 \\ 1-2 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 11 \\ -13 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}\\
\bold{w} &= \begin{pmatrix} 8 \\ -1 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} + 1 \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -4 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 8+1 \\ -1-4 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 9 \\ -5 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}
\end{align*}

The point of intersection is therefore $\boxed{\begin{pmatrix} 11 \\ -13 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}}.$
