(a_1 + a_2 + \dots + a_{12})^2 &\le (1^2 + 1^2 + \dots + 1^2)(a_1^2 + a_2^2 + \dots + a_{12}^2)\\
&= 12(a_1^2 + a_2^2 + \dots + a_{12}^2).
\end{align*}
Since $a_1 + a_2 + \dots + a_{12} = 1,$ we have
\begin{align*}
1 &= (a_1 + a_2 + \dots + a_{12})^2\\
&\le 12(a_1^2 + a_2^2 + \dots + a_{12}^2)\\
&\Rightarrow\qquad a_1^2 + a_2^2 + \dots + a_{12}^2 &\ge \frac{1}{12}.
\end{align*}
Equality holds when $a_1 = a_2 = \dots = a_{12} = \frac{1}{12},$ so the minimum value of $a_1^2 + a_2^2 + \dots + a_{12}^2$ is $\boxed{\frac{1}{12}}.$
Final Answer: The final answer is \frac{1}{12}. I hope it is correct.

