We have that $\text{proj}_{\bold{w}} \bold{v} = \left( \frac{\bold{v} \cdot \bold{w}}{\bold{w} \cdot \bold{w}} \right) \bold{w}.$ Therefore, we need to compute $\bold{v} \cdot \bold{w}$ and $\bold{w} \cdot \bold{w}$.
\begin{align*}
\bold{v} \cdot \bold{w} &= \begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ -4 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 2 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} \\
&= 0 + (-8) + (-1) \\
&= -9
\end{align*}
\begin{align*}
\bold{w} \cdot \bold{w} &= \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 2 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 2 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} \\
&= 4 + 4 + 1 \\
&= 9
\end{align*}
Therefore, $\text{proj}_{\bold{w}} \bold{v} = \left( \frac{-9}{9} \right) \bold{w} = \boxed{\begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ -2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}}.$
