There are 7 letters in the word ELLIPSE: E, L, L, I, P, S, and E. We can arrange these letters in 7! ways. However, since there are 2 L's and 2 E's, we need to divide 7! by 2! and 2! to account for these repeated letters.

\begin{aligned} 7! &= 7 \cdot 6 \cdot 5 \cdot 4 \cdot 3 \cdot 2 \cdot 1 \\ &= 5040 \end{aligned}

Divide by 2! and 2!:

\begin{aligned} 5040 \div 2! \div 2! &= 5040 \div 2 \cdot 2 \\ &= 5040 \div 4 \\ &= 1260 \end{aligned}

So, there are \boxed{1260} ways to arrange the letters of the word ELLIPSE.

