We want to find the values of $t$ and $s$ for which the vector equation of the plane and the line intersect.  We substitute the line equation into the plane equation to get
\begin{align*}
\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 6 \\ 7 \end{pmatrix} + t \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} + s \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -3 \\ -5 \end{pmatrix} &= \begin{pmatrix} 7 \\ 4 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} + u \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 0 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}\\
\Leftrightarrow\qquad \begin{pmatrix} 1 + 2t + 2s \\ 6 - t - 3s \\ 7 - t - 5s \end{pmatrix} &= \begin{pmatrix} 7 + 3u \\ 4 \\ 1 - u \end{pmatrix}\\
\Leftrightarrow\qquad \begin{pmatrix} 2t + 2s - 6 \\ t + 3s - 4 \\ t + 5s - 6 \end{pmatrix} &= \begin{pmatrix} -6 \\ 0 \\ -6 \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} 3u \\ 0 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}\\
